CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 14, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "...She was one of the models in fashion revue at May-Stern auditorium, Monday evening. This show was sponsored for the benefit of a scholarship fund which as been established by the Toujours Fideles Club to aid some worthy youth seeking a college education.  A large crowd packed both the auditorium and the lobby to see the glamorous models on parade.  This show will become an annual event. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Woman modeling dark dress, light colored coat with dark trim, and veil over face, posed in front of painted stone wall, for benefit fashion show in May - Stern furniture store auditorium
